			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About the role:</strong></p>
<p>
We need someone who can take complex technical information and translate it into text (as well as occasional video and images) that is easy to understand. We think that extremely well written documentation is an important first step to providing high quality customer service and we want an individual who is a devotee of customer service first, and a writer second. Our ideal candidate thrives on the potential to reduce chaos, clarify the complex, and keep a variety of audiences in the loop.</p>
<p>
The Technical Writer is responsible for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Planning, organizing, writing, and editing web-based employee and user documentation related to A Small Orange products, a leading provider of Web Hosting and Cloud Services.</li>
<li>
Developing, coordinating, maintaining, and publishing service changes.</li>
<li>
Working with Customer Service, Sales, and Technology departments in a fast-paced environment to create end user and system administrator documentation.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We are looking for:</strong></p>
<p>
A highly organized self-starter that can work independently in a fast-paced environment, and produce multiple deliverables with varying deadlines. A creative problem solver with the flexibility to learn new products and technologies quickly. This position will report to the Director of Customer Service.</p>
<p>
<strong>What you&#39;ll do in this role:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Plan, design, research, write and edit a range of new and existing documents, including: user guides, implementation guides, online help, getting started guides, quick reference guides and style sheets.</li>
<li>
Write documents that can be understood by both technical and non-technical audiences, and may include process flows, diagrams, and narratives.</li>
<li>
Test your work to ensure document accuracy and completeness.</li>
<li>
Create screen shots and illustrations using graphic tools.</li>
<li>
Translate technical requirements and software specifications into user documentation.</li>
<li>
Interview and embed with Developers, Customer Service, Product Management, Project Managers, Trainers, Sales and technical SMEs.</li>
<li>
Contribute to the improvement of documentation standards, tools and processes.</li>
<li>
Understand how documentation is used by clients and update based on any feedback we receive.</li>
<li>
Ensure that we maintain proper User Document Management System (DMS) procedures for revision control. You will also be responsible for our document management.</li>
<li>
Research and acquire product knowledge by means of product requirement documents, talking to stakeholder&rsquo;s formal reviews and the hands-on use of product modules and prototypes.</li>
<li>
Live on the leading edge of company products and services; must have an &lsquo;early adopter&rsquo; mentality.</li>
<li>
All other duties and responsibilities as assigned.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skills required:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Minimum 2-4 years of technical writing experience. The ideal candidate will have at least 3 years technical writing experience, preferably in SaaS based software.</li>
<li>
Strong language skills; demonstrable understanding of the rules of English grammar and usage; experience in organizing and writing highly technical information without losing sight of the needs and aptitude of the audience.</li>
<li>
Strong documentation skills and working with templates and style guidelines for branding consistency.</li>
<li>
Experience writing about web hosting, web hosting software applications</li>
<li>
Experience with screen capture and authoring software</li>
<li>
Ability to absorb and retain complex processes.</li>
<li>
Effective verbal and written communicator with a strong ability to connect with peers, management and cross-functional areas of the company.</li>
<li>
You&#39;re a curious person, with the ability to get along with a wide range of personality types.</li>
<li>
Expert multi-tasker, and effective in high pressure environments.Keen attention to detail while maintaining the ability to see the big picture.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
